President Obama announced his intent to nominate Dan Tangherlini as the Administrator of the General Services Administration. Tangherlini is currently the Acting Administrator of the General Services Administration, a role he has held since April 2012. Prior to this, he served as the Chief Financial Officer at the U.S. Department of the Treasury and also as the Assistant Secretary for Management from 2009 to 2012. Tangherlini has a background in public service, having served as the District of Columbia City Administrator and Deputy Mayor from 2006 to 2009. He has also held various positions in transportation and finance departments. Tangherlini received his education from the University of Chicago and the Wharton School of Business at the University of Pennsylvania. President Obama commended Tangherlini for his leadership and his efforts to make the General Services Administration more efficient, accountable, and transparent.